---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout hideNavbar={true}>

  <section class="min-h-screen px-6 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <h1 
        class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 text-shadow-purple text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
      >
        Why One Piece Feels Bigger Than Ever Right Now
      </h1>

      <p 
        class="text-lg text-gray-400 mb-3 text-center"
        data-aos="fade-right"
        data-aos-delay="100"
      >
        Between the anime, live action, manga and global hype, One Piece is reaching a whole new peak.
      </p>

      <p
        class="text-sm text-gray-500 text-center mb-12"
        data-aos="fade-right"
        data-aos-delay="150"
      >
        March 28, 2026 · 2 min read
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed">

        <!-- Opening -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="200">
          <p>
            I'm a big anime fan. Naruto is still my favorite, no debate.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            But One Piece right now? It's operating on a completely different level.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Scale -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="300">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Scale</h2>
          <p>
            This isn't just hype. The numbers are actually crazyy.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The manga has crossed <span class="text-primary font-bold">600 million copies</span> in about 28 years.
            Superman comics took around 88 years to reach similar numbers. Let that sink in...
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Anime -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="400">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Anime</h2>
          <p>
            The recent arcs like Wano and Egghead have been something else entirely. The animation, the moments, the collective screaming online every time something big drops... it stopped feeling like a weekly show and started feeling like a cultural event. And then <span class="text-primary font-bold">Gear 5</span> happened..... Luffy literally became a cartoon character mid-fight and somehow that was the coolest thing ever. It makes no sense. I love it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Real World Impact -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="500">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Real World Impact</h2>
          <p>
            Here's where it gets genuinely crazy.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            One Piece has influenced real protests and movements in places like 
            <span class="text-primary">Indonesia, Nepal, Brazil</span> and more.
            People using themes of freedom and rebellion from a pirate anime in actual real life situations.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The <span class="text-primary font-bold">Straw Hat Jolly Roger</span> showed up not as merch but as a symbol of resistance and standing up against authority. Oda really wrote something and accidentally made it mean everything to a lot of people.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Live Action -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="600">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">The Live Action</h2>
          <p>
            And then there's the live action. Which somehow, against all odds, did not flop.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The casting did a lot of heavy lifting. 
            <span class="text-primary">Iñaki Godoy (Luffy), Mackenyu (Zoro), Emily Rudd (Nami), Jacob Romero (Usopp), Taz Skylar (Sanji)</span>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            They didn't just look the part. They actually felt like the characters, which is the hard part nobody expected them to nail. I guess that's what happens when the writer himself selects the cast. Like is there anything this man can't do?! Its wild.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Why it works -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="700">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Why It Works</h2>
          <p>
            One Piece fully commits to its world. No half measures, no playing it safe.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            It's weird, emotional, and completely chaotic. And somehow that's exactly why it hits so hard for so many people.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Ending -->
        <div data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="800">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Finally</h2>
          <p>
            Still a Naruto fan. That's not changing.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            But what One Piece is pulling off right now isn't just a popularity spike.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            It genuinely feels like watching history happen in real time. And we're lucky to be around for it.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            On that note:
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            "Kaizoku ou ni ore wa naru!!"
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>